pageContext.claim: “And we also want to have fair [trade] deals where we can do well too. Not just everybody else. Right now, every nation in the world does well with us; we don't do well with them.”
pageContext.analysis: It's not that hard to find countries with which the U.S. runs a trade surplus in goods. At the top of the list are Hong Kong, the Netherlands, the United Arab Emirates, Belgium and Australia.
